ablado= WE have spoken <br /><br />Notice that the past participle does not change in any way. Only the verb HABER conjugates.<br /><br />More examples that include subjunctive:<br />Dudo que hayas estado enfermo= I doubt that you have been ill. (reason: doubt)<br />Es bueno que hayas comido=It is good that you have eaten. (reason: emotion)<br />Espero que hayan estudiado=I hope that you all have studied. (reason: wishing)</font></td></tr></table></center></body></html>';


